jobapi.jd:
A UI developer, or User Interface developer, creates user-friendly software by writing computer code. Their job description includes: 
Designing UIs: Deciding how the user interface (UI) will look and feel 
Researching users: Studying how users interact with the technology to improve system operability 
Creating prototypes: Building wireframes and prototypes to test usability 
Iterating designs: Optimizing designs to improve user satisfaction 
Testing programs: Ensuring that the finished programs are user-friendly 
Collaborating with designers: Working with UI designers to create a coherent and visually appealing UI 
UI developers should have strong time management skills, and be able to prioritize responsibilities. They should also have a good understanding of HTML, JavaScript, and CSS. 
Success in a UI developer role is demonstrated by improving user experience scores and the ease of use of applications.
